Abzakovo (, , Ab≈∫aq) is a rural locality (a village) in Mukasovsky Selsoviet, Baymaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 144 as of 2010. There are 3 streets.
Geography
Abzakovo is located 60 km northeast of Baymak (the district's administrative centre) by road. Akhmerovo is the nearest rural locality.
Ethnicity
The village is inhabited by Bashkirs.
